result.execSummary:
The defendant Shelley L Paplham was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intentionally Subject an Individual at Risk to Abuse - Not Causing or Not Likely/Cause Bodily Harm, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.285(2)(a)1.
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Shelley L Paplham in court with attorney Peter M Wolff.  Andrea M. Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 2, 3 and 4.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 1 is dismissed and read in.  

The Court Orders the Following:

COUNT 2

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

90 Days Jail  (Credit - 1 day) 

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
- No violent contact with C.A.P. all other contact at discretion of the agent;
- Defendant to not have any responsibility to give care to the elderly;
- Follow all orders of Court's with competent jurisdiction.

Costs: $243.00 

Condition Time: 20 days Jail  - Stayed and to be used at the agent's discretion.  Agent can impose Straight Time or Huber



COUNT 3

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

90 Days Jail

Term of Probation: 2 Years  CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2

Conditions of Probation: SAME AS COUNT 2

Costs: $243.00 


COUNT 4

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

90 Days Jail

Term of Probation: 2 Years  CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2

Conditions of Probation:  SAME AS COUNT 2

Costs: $ 243.00
